It is cash only which def effected how much we ordered. We ordered to go. We got tacos Al pastor, veggie quesidilla, horchata and Milanesa torta. The wait was extremely long to go. Took them 1 hour and we were standing there and they didn't keep us updated saying ours was next or here's some free dessert or anything. All we got was a mumbled "perdon" (sorry) as he handed us the bag of food. It is a small place bit has good amount of seating. They speak English and Spanish but it seems to be more of a family owned restaurant. When we got our bag of food to go and brought it back we did not get any plastic forks or spoons or any napkins at all. Horrible. Felt like they kept on serving other customers before us even though we got there first. I would not go back. They are riding on the fact that they are across from Kings theater so of course they will always have customers. The food was not that good. My quesidilla was vegetable and everything was falling apart as I tried to take bites and eat it, it had no seasoning.

I really wanted to love this place.  Situated across Flatbush Avenue from the historic King's Theatre, the location can't be beat. It's perfect for a bite before or after a show. The staff are incredibly friendly! The decor is warm and cozy, but not too crowded, and they feature USB outlets along one wall for charging up while you eat. I think this is a very nice touch.  There were no chips and salsa given to the table. They are instead on the menu as an appetizer. Chips and salsa are a traditional part of dining at a Mexican restaurant and I always look forward to tasting the house's sauce.  It's the first place I've ever been that charges outright. The chips do seem to be made in-house and were light and crispy.  Overall I was a little let down and won't be in a hurry to return, but I'll be back to try other items.  I would recommend giving Los Tres Chiflados a try. The location and friendly staff make it worth a visit.
